</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="1F7302A884521A544A83F990E8E332E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Lacking further material and observations on living individuals, which are of great diagnostic importance in galeommatids, we refrained from assigning a definitive specific name to our shell. However, the overall shape, hinge dentition and the presence of radial sculpture match well descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="4CE2D96DB6CD23E0829D06DBE6558642" authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Taki" authorityYear="1961" class="Coccolithophyceae" family="Galeommatidae" genus="Scintilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scintilla violescens" order="Galeommatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="violescens">
<emphasis id="D86D500803FBB803FF99DABD735AD5D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scintilla violescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Taki, 1961 (
<bibRefCitation id="698DDC061D3AE47F89AC8A0CA11DB42D" author="Arakawa, KY" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 146" refId="B25" refString="Arakawa, KY, 1961. A note on the animal of Scintilla violescens collected in Genkai Sea. Venus 21: 143 - 146" title="A note on the animal of Scintilla violescens collected in Genkai Sea." volume="21" year="1961">Arakawa 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2B7C9CEC55E4F1ED481FB4715A5BAA8E" author="Kuroda, T" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="141 - 142" refId="B126" refString="Kuroda, T, Taki, I, 1961. On a new species of Scintilla (Galeommatidae) from Japan. Venus 21: 141 - 142" title="On a new species of Scintilla (Galeommatidae) from Japan." volume="21" year="1961">Kuroda and Taki 1961</bibRefCitation>
), a species recorded from the intertidal and shallow subtidal of Thailand and Japan (
<bibRefCitation id="7503C77C0CCC8DD8923D5BF7B2E0E959" author="Huber, M" journalOrPublisher="ConchBooks, Harxheim" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B111" refString="Huber, M, 2015. Compendium of bivalves 2. ConchBooks, Harxheim" title="Compendium of bivalves 2." year="2015">Huber 2015</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast to our shell, however, 
<bibRefCitation id="C24463AA9775FA072F1EAB113E7289B9" author="Kuroda, T" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="141 - 142" refId="B126" refString="Kuroda, T, Taki, I, 1961. On a new species of Scintilla (Galeommatidae) from Japan. Venus 21: 141 - 142" title="On a new species of Scintilla (Galeommatidae) from Japan." volume="21" year="1961">Kuroda and Taki (1961)</bibRefCitation>
mention the presence of radial sculpture on the entire surface of the valves of their type material. While our Mediterranean shell is less elongated than the specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="5206DABCEE92271DDAE7BF83FA1DF37F" genus="S." lsidName="S. violescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violescens">
<emphasis id="4DEB0EE5C7FCA8E4343B0A88A4E778D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="E4806CEC8EA3021120AC6A5A05A2C401" author="Okutani, T" journalOrPublisher="Tokai University Press, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B164" refString="Okutani, T, 2000. Marine mollusks in Japan. Tokai University Press, Tokyo" title="Marine mollusks in Japan." year="2000">Okutani (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="18031DA453E2DEB28697E655E9398596" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" author="Luetzen, J" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="261 - 308" refId="B136" refString="Luetzen, J, Nielsen, C, 2005. Galeommatid bivalves from Phuket, Thailand. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 144: 261 - 308, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" title="Galeommatid bivalves from Phuket, Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" volume="144" year="2005">
<normalizedToken id="028702956D4134DD1DC14B3F5074294F" originalValue="Lützen">Luetzen</normalizedToken>
and Nielsen (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EDE9543F18D5925DE97E575AC5E81E5D" author="Huber, M" journalOrPublisher="ConchBooks, Harxheim" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B111" refString="Huber, M, 2015. Compendium of bivalves 2. ConchBooks, Harxheim" title="Compendium of bivalves 2." year="2015">Huber (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, it is very similar in outline to the shell shown by 
<bibRefCitation id="D43FCBE3AD03C53BC8088C7DE17F1A3C" author="Arakawa, KY" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 146" refId="B25" refString="Arakawa, KY, 1961. A note on the animal of Scintilla violescens collected in Genkai Sea. Venus 21: 143 - 146" title="A note on the animal of Scintilla violescens collected in Genkai Sea." volume="21" year="1961">Arakawa (1961</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5B) (which was identified by T. Kuroda and I. Taki). 
<taxonomicName id="95179668D0AF7FE8665F794C469C5526" authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Taki" authorityYear="1961" class="Coccolithophyceae" family="Galeommatidae" genus="Scintilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scintilla violescens" order="Galeommatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="violescens">
<emphasis id="AEE9043213271743554E63A1AFDFB6B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scintilla violescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be variable also with respect to shell size and coloration: specimens from Thailand (maximum length = 10.5 mm, n = 12 spcms) all were considerably smaller than the&gt; 15 mm-long Japanese type (
<bibRefCitation id="CC2D30A04FEBB2EEDABF1E8E2A50E6ED" author="Kuroda, T" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="141 - 142" refId="B126" refString="Kuroda, T, Taki, I, 1961. On a new species of Scintilla (Galeommatidae) from Japan. Venus 21: 141 - 142" title="On a new species of Scintilla (Galeommatidae) from Japan." volume="21" year="1961">Kuroda and Taki 1961</bibRefCitation>
) and had a whitish instead of pale violet color (
<bibRefCitation id="EB0B9E04E9BEBF0F059F7F53B639E685" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" author="Luetzen, J" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="261 - 308" refId="B136" refString="Luetzen, J, Nielsen, C, 2005. Galeommatid bivalves from Phuket, Thailand. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 144: 261 - 308, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" title="Galeommatid bivalves from Phuket, Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" volume="144" year="2005">
<normalizedToken id="ECBF30CE401FBE6F667E2E3F442E3122" originalValue="Lützen">Luetzen</normalizedToken>
and Nielsen 2005
</bibRefCitation>
), like the Israeli shell. Considering this great plasticity in shell characters, and the differences in living animal morphology observed for Thai vs. Japanese specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="E897E0281A24111748AEA6269E989F95" genus="S." lsidName="S. violescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violescens">
<emphasis id="C970DCB4551C97654899AEFF0FA46424" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="92F05DAE95D856534C1DE8FE50EA24B7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" author="Luetzen, J" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="261 - 308" refId="B136" refString="Luetzen, J, Nielsen, C, 2005. Galeommatid bivalves from Phuket, Thailand. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 144: 261 - 308, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" title="Galeommatid bivalves from Phuket, Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00168.x" volume="144" year="2005">
<normalizedToken id="8103E3C6DF1A643459401FE5D996FE91" originalValue="Lützen">Luetzen</normalizedToken>
and Nielsen (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
, the question arises whether more than one biological entity might be involved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51F597EF2C22E1B077AB3DD67EB25467" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Irrespective of its unresolved specific affinity, the shell presented here clearly differs from all native Mediterranean galeommatids and thus cannot be confused; it can be easily distinguished from the non-indigneous 
<taxonomicName id="2A5374CACDF8E35F2196BC59CB1FFEB3" authorityName="Luetzen &amp; Nielsen, 2005 (sensu Mifsud and Ovalis" authorityYear="2012" class="Bivalvia" family="Galeommatidae" genus="Nudiscintilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nudiscintilla glabra" order="Galeommatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="glabra">Nudiscintilla cf. glabra</taxonomicName>
(see above) by its less elongated shell, smaller L:H-ratio and, most notably, the presence of radial sculpture on the valves. Apart from the present shell, which was found in 1999 in Haifa Bay, we know of no other material.
</paragraph>
